eristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Blenkinsop","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(2010: NA)","English (northern): habitational name from a place called Blenkinsopp in Northumberland. Compare   Blankenship   and   Blankinship  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Blankenship","meanings":["English (northern): variant of   Blenkinsop  . See also   Blankinship  , compare   Blakenship  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret De Blenkinsop was born in 1324, in Haltwhistle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, her father, Thomas de Blankenship, was 24 and her mother, Margaret Strother, was 21. She married Alan Strother about 1345, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died in Greenhead, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1324–":"1324–Surnud","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","1356–Male":"1356–Surnud","1326–1381":"1326–1381","1348–1408":"1348–1408","1349–1424":"1349–1424","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1300–1388":"1300–1388","1303–1382":"1303–1382","Abt 1345":"umbes 1345","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1349":"1349","1348":"1348","1326":"1326","1303":"1303","1424":"1424","1324":"1324","about 1349":"umbes 1349","1356":"1356","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","about 1348":"umbes 1348","1408":"1408","Blenkinsop Castle, Greenhead/Haltwhistle, Northumberland, England":"Greenhead, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Haltwhistle, Northumberland, England":"Haltwhistle, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lanton, Northumberland, England":"Lanton, Northumberland, England",", Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England"},"fi":{"1324–":"1324–Kuollut","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","1356–Male":"1356–Kuollut","1326–1381":"1326–1381","1348–1408":"1348–1408","1349–1424":"1349–1424","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1300–1388":"1300–1388","1303–1382":"1303–1382","Abt 1345":"noin 1345","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1349":"1349","1348":"1348","1326":"1326","1303":"1303","1424":"1424","1324":"1324","about 1349":"noin 1349","1356":"1356","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","about 1348":"noin 1348","1408":"1408","Blenkinsop Castle, Greenhead/Haltwhistle, Northumberland, England":"Greenhead, Northumberland, En